Anna Okon The Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency has extended the validity of statutory and trading certificates for all Nigerian registered vessels. The certificates include Standards of Training, Certification and Watchkeeping certificates for seafarers issued by the agency. The Director-General, NIMASA, Dr Bashir Jamoh, was quoted in a statement signed by the Head, Corporate Communications, NIMASA, Philip Kyanet, as saying that NIMASA remained committed to implementing its mandates during the COVID-19 crisis. Jamoh said it was necessary to ensure uninterrupted shipping despite the pandemic, stressing that shipping was one of the major ways of moving medical aids across the globe. “Our determination to ensure that shipping continues during this trying time remains unwavering and this is why we have continued to come up with measures to keep the global shipping chain moving in line with the recommendations of the International Maritime Organisation,” he stated. The NIMASA boss said the agency was aware of the difficulties seafarers would be facing and the need to keep them in jobs even beyond the pandemic. Copyright PUNCH.
